(# ELECTROSTATICS - LONG BRIEF ANSWERS \(Class 11\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Q1. Define linear charge density, surface charge density and volume charge density.) Tj
T*
(Write their SI units.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(When electric charge is distributed over a body, its distribution is described using) Tj
T*
(charge densities.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. **Linear Charge Density \(lambda\):**) Tj
T*
(   It is defined as the amount of electric charge per unit length of a charged conductor) Tj
T*
(   or wire.) Tj
T*
(   Formula: lambda = dq/dl) Tj
T*
(   SI unit: coulomb per metre \(C m^-1\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(2. **Surface Charge Density \(sigma\):**) Tj
T*
(   It is the amount of electric charge distributed per unit area of a charged surface.) Tj
T*
(   Formula: sigma = dq/dA) Tj
T*
(   SI unit: coulomb per square metre \(C m^-2\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(3. **Volume Charge Density \(rho\):**) Tj
T*
(   It is the amount of electric charge per unit volume of a charged body.) Tj
T*
(   Formula: rho = dq/dV) Tj
T*
(   SI unit: coulomb per cubic metre \(C m^-3\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Q2. State and prove Gauss's law of electrostatics.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Statement of Gauss's Law:) Tj
T*
(The total electric flux through any closed surface is equal to \(1/epsilon0\) times the) Tj
T*
(total charge enclosed by the surface.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Integral form: Integral\(E . dS\) over closed surface = Q/epsilon0) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Proof:) Tj
T*
(Consider a point charge q placed at the centre of a spherical Gaussian surface of radius) Tj
T*
(r.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Electric field on the surface:) Tj
T*
(E = \(1/4*pi*epsilon0\) * \(q/r^2\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Electric flux through the surface:) Tj
T*
(Phi = Integral\(E . dS\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Since E is constant over the spherical surface and acts radially outward:) Tj
T*
(Phi = E * Integral\(dS\) = E * \(4*pi*r^2\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Substitute E:) Tj
ET
endstream
