(Phi = \(1/4*pi*epsilon0\) * \(q/r^2\) * 4*pi*r^2 = q/epsilon0) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Hence, Integral\(E . dS\) over closed surface = q/epsilon0.) Tj
T*
(Therefore, Gauss's law is proved.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Q3. What are electric lines of force? Explain their properties.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Electric lines of force are imaginary continuous curves drawn in an electric field such) Tj
T*
(that the tangent at any point gives the direction of the electric field at that point.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Properties:) Tj
T*
(1. Electric field lines originate from positive charges and terminate on negative charges.) Tj
T*
(2. No two electric field lines can intersect each other.) Tj
T*
(3. The density of field lines represents the strength of the electric field.) Tj
T*
(4. Electric field lines are perpendicular to the surface of a conductor.) Tj
T*
(5. Electric field lines do not form closed loops.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Q4. Define electric field and electric field intensity. Write its SI unit.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Electric field at a point is the region around a charged body in which it exerts a force) Tj
T*
(on another charge.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Electric field intensity is defined as the force experienced by a unit positive test) Tj
T*
(charge placed at that point.) Tj
T*
(Formula: E = F/q) Tj
T*
(SI unit: newton per coulomb \(N C^-1\) or volt per metre \(V m^-1\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Q5. State and explain Coulomb's law and law of conservation of charge.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Coulomb's Law:) Tj
T*
(The force of attraction or repulsion between two point charges is:) Tj
T*
(- directly proportional to the product of their charges) Tj
T*
(- inversely proportional to the square of the distance between them) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Formula: F = \(1/4*pi*epsilon0\) * \(q1*q2/r^2\)) Tj
T*
(The force acts along the line joining the two charges.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(### Law of Conservation of Charge:) Tj
T*
(Electric charge can neither be created nor destroyed, but it can be transferred from one) Tj
T*
(body to another.) Tj
T*
(The total charge of an isolated system remains constant.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Q6. What is an electric dipole? Derive the expression for torque acting on an electric) Tj
T*
(dipole placed in a uniform electric field.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(An electric dipole consists of two equal and opposite charges separated by a small) Tj
ET
