(## Q7. Derive expression for electric field intensity on the axial line of an electric) Tj
T*
(dipole.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Consider a dipole with charges +q and -q separated by distance 2a.) Tj
T*
(Let point P be at distance r from the centre on the axial line.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Net electric field at P:) Tj
T*
(E = \(1/4*pi*epsilon0\) * [q/\(r-a\)^2 - q/\(r+a\)^2]) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(For r >> a, after simplification:) Tj
T*
(E_axial = \(1/4*pi*epsilon0\) * \(2p/r^3\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Direction of the field is along the dipole moment.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Q8. State Coulomb's law in vector form and explain the terms.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Vector form of Coulomb's law:) Tj
T*
(F12 = \(1/4*pi*epsilon0\) * \(q1*q2/r^2\) * rhat12) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Where:) Tj
T*
(- rhat12 is the unit vector from charge q1 to q2.) Tj
T*
(- The force acts along the line joining the two charges.) Tj
ET
